\s2 The why of parables
\p 
\v 10 \w But|strong="G2532"\w* \w when|strong="G3753"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1096"\w* \w alone|strong="G3441"\w*, \w those|strong="G3588"\w* \w who|strong="G3588"\w* \w were|strong="G3588"\w* \w around|strong="G4012"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w with|strong="G4862"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w twelve|strong="G1427"\w*,\f + \fr 4:10 \ft Evidently there were some regular followers beyond the twelve. In fact, later on He would send out seventy, two by two (Luke 10:1).\f* \w asked|strong="G2065"\w* \w Him|strong="G3588"\w* \w about|strong="G4012"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w parable|strong="G3850"\w*.
