\v 21 \w So|strong="G2532"\w* \w He|strong="G2532"\w* \w said|strong="G3004"\w* \w to|strong="G2532"\w* \w them|strong="G3004"\w*, “\w How|strong="G4920"\w* \w is|strong="G2532"\w* \w it|strong="G2532"\w* \w that|strong="G2532"\w* \w you|strong="G3004"\w* \w still|strong="G3768"\w* don't \w understand|strong="G4920"\w*?”\f + \fr 8:21 \ft It is easy to criticize those disciples as slow learners, and indeed the Lord was evidently unhappy with them, but I wonder if we would have done any better.\f*
\s1 A blind man
\p 
